Bats are not spooky or scary in Chinese culture (but because it is #halloween2021, we'll show them here anyway), but very lucky symbols. This is because the word for 'bat' in Chinese is a homophone of (i.e. sounds like) the word for 'good fortune'.
@BrightonMuseums https://t.co/LNqeyFI0QP

Frederick Crace never travelled to China, but he and his father John Crace purchased, collected and traded Asian porcelain and other export ware. It is likely he would have seen these vases. Details from the Crace drawing and the Chinese vase (both on display @BrightonMuseums): https://t.co/7fAKNycH9a

To mark #halloween2021, here are some cute bats drawn by Frederick Crace in c.1815 for the interiors of the Royal Pavilion, Brighton @BrightonMuseums.
